        "title": "fix(memory): warn on high runtime watcher pressure",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- re-add the memory-watch FD pressure warning after #89246 reverted the earlier warning-only PR\n- keep memory watching enabled by default and warn only when runtime watcher state is already large enough to be risky\n- move the warning out of config validation so normal startup config loading does not recursively scan memory folders\n- cover both built-in memory watching and QMD collection watching with focused watcher tests\n\n## Related\n\n- Replaces the warning behavior reverted by #89246.\n- Follow-up to #89185, but now self-contained because #89185 was reverted.\n- Refs #86613, where FD pressure was reproduced with large watched memory trees.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/memory-core/src/memory/manager.watcher-config.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/memory-core/src/memory/qmd-manager.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/config/validation.policy.test.ts`\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/config/validation.policy.test.ts extensions/memory-core/src/memory/manager-sync-ops.ts extensions/memory-core/src/memory/manager.watcher-config.test.ts extensions/memory-core/src/memory/qmd-manager.ts extensions/memory-core/src/memory/qmd-manager.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check`\n",
